#
#*  This sample HIT/CLOU text component tests the use case of multiple sequentiel
    fields in the XML input data.   #

Let's test away with multiple fields.@
The correct output would look like this:@
Group 1 Line 1@
Group 1 Line 2@
Group 1 Line 3@
Group 1 Line 4@
Group 2 Line 1@
Group 2 Line 2@
Group 2 Line 3@
Group 2 Line 4@
Group 3 Line 1@
Group 3 Line 2@
Group 3 Line 3@
Group 3 Line 4@
@And this is what we get:@@

#L group1 D {}
#L group2 D {}
#L group3 D {}

#D lelement ""

#X< lelement
#S lelement <> "*" :
    #L group1 & { lelement }
    #X< lelement
#

#X< lelement
#S lelement <> "*" :
    #L group2 & { lelement }
    #X< lelement
#

#X< lelement
#S lelement <> "*" :
    #L group3 & {lelement }
    #X< lelement
#

#D counter 1
#W listlen("group1")
    #> group1[counter]@
    #= counter counter + 1
#
#= counter 1
#W listlen("group2")
    #> group2[counter]@
    #= counter counter + 1
#
#= counter 1
#W listlen("group3")
    #> group3[counter]@
    #= counter counter + 1
#
